{"title": "How do I programmatically set an Angular 2 form control to dirty?", "tags": ["javascript", "angular2"], "creation_date": 1466018608, "score": 2, "body": "<p>You should use the <code>markAsDirty</code> method, like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>control.markAsDirty();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will also mark all direct ancestors as dirty to maintain the model.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://angular.io/docs/ts/latest/api/forms/index/AbstractControl-class.html#!#markAsDirty-anchor\" rel=\"nofollow\">Docs link</a></p>\n", "last_activity_date": 1477672126, "answer_id": 37844093, "is_accepted": true, "owner": {"user_id": 5862315, "reputation": 1490, "user_type": "registered", "accept_rate": 80, "display_name": "Eran Shabi", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/5862315/eran-shabi", "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f3b5aae9540e6a0802a3ecc0de7656dd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1"}, "last_edit_date": 1477672126, "question_id": 37844092}